# nuclei #6403 — Honeypot Detection Bounty

## Stack
- Language: Go 1.21+
- Repo: projectdiscovery/nuclei (branch: dev)
- Module: github.com/projectdiscovery/nuclei/v3

## Conventions
- All new packages go under `pkg/protocols/common/`
- Logging: `gologger.Warning().Msgf(...)` — never fmt.Println
- Tests: `testify/require`, table-driven where possible
- Concurrency: always acquire per-item lock BEFORE releasing cache lock (see MASTER_PLAN)
- No placeholder comments. Full logic only.

## Critical constraint
The `MarkMatch` race fix is the core differentiator. The item lock MUST be acquired while
the cache lock is still held. Do not release `c.mu` before `item.mu.Lock()`.

## PR target
Branch `dev` on upstream projectdiscovery/nuclei — not main.

---

## Cursor Handoff Protocol (MANDATORY)

After every execution session — whether complete or blocked — update these two files:

### `.context/LEARNINGS.md`
Fill every section. Exact file paths, line numbers, error text. No summaries.
Claude reads this cold. Vague entries are useless.

Required sections:
- **What Was Built** — each file touched, one line per file
- **Patterns Used** — nuclei-specific discoveries (struct layouts, import paths, init order)
- **Decisions Made** — any deviation from MASTER_PLAN and the exact reason
- **Gotchas** — surprises that would have saved time to know earlier
- **Blockers** — if blocked, paste the FULL compiler/runtime error verbatim
- **Open Questions** — anything uncertain for Claude to resolve
- **Test Results** — paste `go test ./pkg/protocols/common/honeypotcache/... -race -count=1 -v` output
- **Build Check** — paste `go build ./...` output

### `.context/STATUS.md`
Change the `status:` frontmatter field to one of:
- `in_progress` — still executing
- `blocked` — hit a hard wall, cannot continue without Claude input
- `done` — `go build ./...` clean, race tests pass, flags appear in `-h`

If `blocked`: write a one-sentence blocker summary under `## Blocking Criteria`.
